reviews.text: Parts of the Capital were under construction when we visited, but overall the structure was still incredibly beautiful. The interior architecture seemed more like something out of a movie than real life; particularly the beautiful golden arches and tilings on the floor. The tour guide we had was very friendly and we were able to enter both the Supreme Court room and the state legislature room.

It was a random trip. We traveled to Lincoln to buy a car. Walked the streets that are lined in a perfect grid. While the tall building is a marvel, the treasure lies inside, dim light, spectacular tall beams, peerless marble work, wall murals, prefect chandeliers, the state house chambers, it has an imposing peaceful and quiet gravitas. The interplay of architecture, light and muted displays create a harmonious experience. The building is the museum. A must see.

The capital is very tall, kind of scary to go all the way to the top. There is a statue on the very top of the tower, he is called 'the tailor' because he sews. With binoculars, one can see the statue is holding a singer sewing machine, such cool history way up there, gives me goose bumps.
One of the most beautiful state capital building in the nation. If you are passing through Lincoln, do not hesitate to stop.
This Capitol building has a beautiful structure.
Just lovely!  Wonderful exhibits and helpful staff.  They offered me a place to hang up my coat and a place to store my bag.  With free admission how could you not stop by?
This is a really nice gallery. The building, designed by Philip Johnson, is a work of art itself. Don’t forget to wander campus to see the various sculptures.
Always love seeing what this gem of a museum building has the show of it'slarge and growing collection of American art.

The building and showcases are nice, and I don't really have anything to complain about. However, I was generally unimpressed by their choice of art pieces and the collections they choose to showcase.
Just wish it was bigger, they had some major art and it was wonderful and unexpected.

A truly great children’s zoo. Are used to buy my grandchildren season passes every year for Christmas when they were preschoolers. They loved the extra train ride tickets grandma would get them and we’re always excited about going to the zoo. Now that the zoo is remodeling and expanding it is going to be even better than before. This is an experience you really should take your children to

This zoo is great for parents and kids alike. The old exhibits are great but I cannot wait to see the new ones! This zoos volunteer program helped teach me about responsibility and how to be a good employee.

We love going here!! It is just the right size to keep my little guy entertained, yet wear him out at the same time. We enjoy the train, and all of the play areas. We can't wait for the girrafes, lions, and monkeys!! We highly recommend this zoo for anyone with young kids.

This is a great place to bring the kids on a nice day. There's plenty to keep them occupied from petting and feeding animals, pony rides, a train ride, and plenty of cool creatures to check out. Capping the trip off at the sandpit where they can dig for dino bones while you grab a bite to eat is a perfect way to end the day. We got our money's worth out of the membership passes in no time!

When I lived in Nebraska my mother signed me up for a "zoo crew" at the Lincoln childrens zoo. I thought I would just be going there and like raking leaves for a day and nothing else. Little did I know that it would be one of the greatest things I have ever done in my life. I was able to basically be an employee at the zoo. I got to show people the animals and Information about them. We would hold the horses while kids would ride them, we would give water tattoos to little kids and let them pet chinchillas. We got to spray kids hands with sugar water to that butterflies would land on their hands. It taught me to respect animals and how to work with other people. This zoo has such an amazing variation of animals and they take care of them so well. I would rate it higher if I could.

Yummy yummy yummy! This place is so good. They were supper busy and we had a big table. And they were awesome! Our server very friendly and did a great job! Food came out fast and hot!! The appetizers were all amazing!! This is one of my favorite restaurants!! I just love this wonderful delicious place!!

It's really a nice and clean place to go eat. The food and drink are great and the price is not too expensive. Easy for a reservation just call before. Friendly customers service. For a party reservation for what I know they do not have a big table that can fit 16 to 20 people. So if you ever want to reserve a spot for about 20 people you have to consider that you might be sitting in two different tables. One table can fit approximately 15 people. By the way I would recommend this place for anything. The location is so easy to find and they are some parking spots around there too.

Best patio in Lincoln, besides maybe the Mill.  Food is okay, beer is okay, but all tastes similar even across styles. For Lincoln, it's fine, and it's very Lincoln. There are more interesting beer bars though. Unfortunately this is the main place to get a beer and a meal and a cool, shaded patio seat in the summer. It's gotten less cool since the arena moved in, but I have fond memories still. And they at least try to offer options to vegetarians. For Nebraska, that's something!

We went there for my mom's birthday and it was a really good choice for the occasion.  Service was excellent and prompt.  The food was great, highly recommend the prime rib.  I will go back anytime.  Parking is hit or miss though.

I really like this place because of all the different types of beer that they brew. I enjoy trying different types of beer and they have a nice variety of different Brews. This is one place I always go to visit when I am in Lincoln. The atmosphere is very warm and inviting and it's great for Family Dining.

A great place for getting that nice social atmosphere. We stopped in on trivia night unintentionally and ended up having a great time. The food was well prepared and well priced. There were also some unique items on the menu which pushes them past the standard, everyday chain restaurants.

Great Louisiana food in Nebraska! The category 5 hurricane is a must for rum lovers. The shrimp appetizer with the buttery Creole flavoring is a meal within itself. I got the fried catfish to go. A lot of food at  reasonable prices. Will definitely return here the next time.

Service was great. Food was overall good. Coming from the south New Orleans style food is pretty common, so we expected a lot.  Hush puppies were sweet and over cooked. Everywhere makes them differently. I ordered the Philly cheese steak the bun was to big for the amount of meat. My husband ordered the combo platter which was definitely worth the money it had a huge portion of fish.
Amazingly delicious! Good service, great food, clean restaurant, lively atmosphere.  I highly recommend the Drunken Monkey drink. Can't wait to go again.
All the food was good. Coleslaw was not to my liking but no fault of theirs. Service was decent. Staff was all very nice. Atmosphere was very authentic feeling.

Best Italian food in Albany. I went here for my birthday and had a great time. The atmosphere, food and dining experience make you feel like you are at a high end restaurant in New York city. The wait staff are amazing and really take care of you. The place is always full. You will leave satisfied.

It's where I will have my last meal if given the choice. Every single dish is amazing, from the salad to dessert. The crab and lobster ravioli is my favorite and last meal of choice. Perfect! The family that runs the place is wonderful and accommodating. The downsides are that the place is small and always crowded. And because of this, I don't get there as much as I would like. One small sore spot is the younger waiter, he is forgetful and inattentive. Everyone else is amazing and goes above and beyond! Best meal to be had in Albany!

The service & staff are very polite & helpful.. The mussel's are awesome the sauce they cook them is so good I use the bread they give you to sop up the sauce it's that GOOD!! The chicken antica is my favorite I get it every time & I crave it on my way up there. I also recommend the veal parmigiana. Absolutely freshest ingredients. Friend said his Chilean sea bass was cooked perfectly. Friendliest and professional service. Be sure to make reservations well ahead for a Friday or Saturday.

We were there for the first time and would go back once a week. First greeted by the mater
De' at the door, he took our coats hung them,
Took us to our seats put our napkins on our laps. Very gracious. Food out of this would. 
Salad crisp, entry Delos, wine smooth, dessert the tops. Can't say anything better 
About the place.
Customer service is the best ive seen in the capital region for a restaurant. Food was was phenomenal. We will be going back for sure.
5 star staff.  Plesent and helpful.  Not the biggest fan of some of the prices, but found some bargains and stocked up.  E-mail deals are great at this store.

Nice clean store, huge and great selection. Was just buying bottle rockets etc for the kids for NYE. A lot of security- the guy at the entrance had a gun!! Everything is kind of expensive, but everything is BOGO- so in the end not too costly, but more than you need.
I liked this fireworks store. They are nice and have a amazing selection of fireworks. This store is way bigger than the Morrisvile store.

Great deals here everything is buy one get one free. Fair prices for what you get. The staff is very helpful and very knowledgeable on their product. You don't have to pretend to know everything when you come in here they don't treat you like an idiot.

Prices are pretty high-1star. They don't sell bricks of jumping jacks...-1 star.
People are nice and helpful :)
I'll be back when they have better promotions :)

Yummy yummy yummy! This place is so good. They were supper busy and we had a big table. And they were awesome! Our server very friendly and did a great job! Food came out fast and hot!! The appetizers were all amazing!! This is one of my favorite restaurants!! I just love this wonderful delicious place!!

For a party reservation for what I know they do not have a big table that can fit 16 to 20 people. So if you ever want to reserve a spot for about 20 people you have to consider that you might be sitting in two different tables. One table can fit approximately 15 people. By the way I would recommend this place for anything. The location is so easy to find and they are some parking spots around there too.

It's gotten less cool since the arena moved in, but I have fond memories still. And they at least try to offer options to vegetarians. For Nebraska, that's something!

We went there for my mom's birthday and it was a really good choice for the occasion.  Service was excellent and prompt.  The food was great, highly recommend the prime rib.  I will go back anytime.  Parking is hit or miss though.

I really like this place because of all the different types of beer that they brew. I enjoy trying different types of beer and they have a nice variety of different Brews. This is one place I always go to visit when I am in Lincoln. The atmosphere is very warm and inviting and it's great for Family Dining.
Five star pizza
Valentionos is my favorite restaurant it is the BEST.
Quick, great pizza, always friendly staff
it was amazing. I don't know how they are world wide

$5.50 for a create your own huge slice of pizza that was so yummy! Such a great atmosphere! Sat up at the bar, because I was in a hurry and the bartender was so nice! Can't wait to go back when I'm not in a hurry!
Awesome pizza! Great selection of beer. Pool tables put it over the top! (For me. I love playing pool)

Neat place to eat, cool decor. Menu had lots of unique pizza toppings, I had the Southern which had ground turkey, artichokes, spinach, mushrooms, onions, and a wine sauce. The crust was thin and crispy and the flavors together were wonderful. the only reason I did not give 5 stars is it is a bit inconvenient to order you have to go up to the counter and when your food is ready they call your name but even after you're finished you have to take your glasses up to the bar and dishes to a different area. A little difficult when you have three young children with you. If the prices reflected that they didn't have to pay wait staff it wouldn't be such a big deal but for having to do all that yourself it was pretty pricey.
Pizza was good...has a very earthy feel to the place.  Had a Hawaiian style pizza.
Diverse menu options with pizza by the slice and made on the spot. My experience at yia yias was a good one. I enjoyed my slice of pizza ( The Greek) and my side salad was good as well.

Margarita Flights.....blended or on the rocks, great for a hot day in downtown. You choose three from a variety of choices. Dinner was really good also. Glad we tried it! Everything was so good!!!! Yummy margaritas and I had a chicken burrito especial and it was one of the best burritos ever!!!! Really nice place and loved the decor! The food was tasty and satisfying, but it was what is typical at authentic, family-run Mexican fare in the middle of Nebraska. The food is made-to-order. I especially appreciated the friendliness of the servers.

The ambience is ok. The food is not at all what is expected from a Mexican restaurant. We ordered fajitas,enchiladas, burritos and tacos and all of them were bad. We just finished our dishes so that food is not wasted. They served the margarita is plastic glasses which was a major turn off. Our server was not able to understand what we were ordering and though it was not that crowded the order was taking a long time. It’s a big no no from my side.

This is one of my favorite spots for Mexican food. Combination number 10 w double rice is my go to. The drinks going out here are quite original and generous pours so don't be fooled by price they are fair. I love the hot plates and wish this method was practiced at more restaurants. Would typically give a 5 star but rice portions were a bit off tonite and server must have had a larger section than normal...

Tasteless. Bland and boring. Menu online not up to date. Asked for refill of chips and they never followed through. Food was cold. Not worth the cost at all. I remember eating there a long time ago and enjoying it, but this most recent time was absolutely awful. Not planning on ever going back again.
Good food. The restaurant looks awesome after the renovation! The owner is a really nice guy and it's always fun to see him and say hello.
One of my favorite places for authentic Mexican food!

Husbands torta was great. My enchiladas tasted a little off but rice and beans were good.  Queso wasn't very good.  Service was awesome and food came out quick. In general a great little place,  will try something different next time.
Great homemade food, friendly service, one of the best Micheladas.
For right now I'm giving 4 out of 5 only because it was my first time and had the carnitas taco combo, Yummy. I'm looking forward to many return visits. Great service as well.
Authentic, fresh, affordable simple Mexican cuisine!

Great fresh food but they need hotter salsa. Maybe it's because it's in Lincoln that they have sorta gringo style but other than that this place is delicious and has generous portions. Come back daily for their lunch specials.
So very tasty.  Like subway but with tortillas...and good food.  Wish we had this back home.

7:45 door licked sign off on one side walk around and stand at the counter with my hungry daughter and get completely ignored for 5 minutes. I understand it was close to closing but making a couple  burritos takes a couple minutes. Lazy hipster turds.

I understand the idea of having a laid back burrito place, however my experience here was gross and needs to be shared. I have been here two times. The second time the servers were clearly under the influence of some type of substance and were really unprofessional. One of them was literally barefoot in the kitchen. I will never eat here again.
Food is pretty good and it's rarely busy. I wasn't able to find a salsa I liked.  They have mini burritos which are a perfect portion.

So bummed! I’ve eaten here in the past but always for supper. Maybe it was because it was lunch. I don’t know... but the pad see yew was incredibly bland! Maybe they used old oil? I love Thai food because of the flavor! I was disappointed today ☹️

Edit: docking one star for their carry out. It used to be ready quickly, however lately it has taken longer and longer for it to be ready. On this occasion it took 50+ minutes from when I ordered and over 15 after I arrived to have one carry out dish ready when they only had 60ish percent of their tables filled. Management did a great job and threw in a free appetizer! Top notch! 

My wife and I love this restaurant. They have carry out that is always ready in less than 20 minutes. Drunken noodles and Thai basil stir fry are our favorites. The only problem is that parking is minimal. If you're going to sit and eat you'll have to park in a garage!
Got take out.  One of the container's lids cracked on the way home.  Messy, but the food was yummy.
Classy Thai place without being too expensive. Food was delicious and plentiful.
Unique place in downtown Lincoln. Good food and great atmosphere. No complaints.

You can never go wrong with Ivanna Cone, definitely the total package when it comes to ice cream experience. Awesome location, fun decorations, great service, and of course delicious ice cream. The only "complaint" I have is that they don't accept card but that's not too big of a deal because there's an ATM in the building if I forget.

Been many times before and never disappointed. Bit pricey compared to other ice cream shops but it's local and made each day so I don't mind paying a bit extra. Took my husband there for the first time and he liked it.
Super great ice cream with very nice staff. They do not accept EFT, but there is an ATM right outside to get cash. Connected to a fun bookstore as well!
Best place in town to get ice cream. Fun flavors that change often. Pretty small place so I recommend you get it to go. Addition of a window to order from in Art Alley really helps wait times.
Best I’ve ever had. Simply amazing. Make sure you get a waffle cone!

My favorite restaurant in town! I am never disappointed with the quality of food and with the great customer service. I tried their taro bubble tea for the first time here yesterday and its my new favorite in town. Ive gone to many other places and this one, by far, has the best tapioca.

Walking up to the complex, the appearance gave me some negative expectations. The food turned out to be fantastic as was the service. It was my first time eating Vietnamese food, and I will be returning here for the second. Thanks! Try the rice noodle with beef and shrimp. Large!
A prime example of the phrase looks are deceiving. This place doesn't look like much, but the food is absolutely amazing as well as the service! This place is a new favorite for my family.
I always enjoy my experience here. The food, the smell, the atmosphere, the staff are all great. I would recommend this place to anyone.
Best place to eat in town! Great family owned restaurant with excellent food!

They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.
Quiet place, very friendly staff and a broad enough menu to keep everyone guessing what they want. Lunch specials are around $10 with most entrees around $14. Great place for a quick bite.

Everyone here was so extremly nice to me and they all were stop helpful! (I've never eaten Thai before) The food was great, the drink was great & the service was just awesome! I wish all places were as friendly as they were here!

Came in today. Waited 45 mins thinking the food is almost ready. When I go and ask the worker about the wait time for food, she says it will take another 10 mins. Canceled the order and left with no food. Who takes 50+ mins to cook during lunch hour. Plus it was only one person serving all the customers and it took some time before she came to take our order. If you know it's going to be busy, have more people to help during peak hours. This is unacceptable. I would not give a star but that's the only option available. I would not recommend this place.

You couldn't ask for a better Panda the green beans and chicken was better than I've had anywhere it was super unlike the one that's over by the Vallarta store on Clinton and Weber this one here gets an A+ and that one over there gets an F don't bother to go there cuz their food is terrible. Also the help over here on Shaw is much more friendly and it's an all-around better experience
Place is decorated really nice for the holidays and food/service is good. Karaoke in the summer....

The food is GREAT especially the steak sandwich and crab Patty
My drink of choice would be the Margarita up. Not on the rocks.
I love the Brass Rail!! Good food.
Not pricey Been going there for about 40 yrs.

Great local place. Food is very good and they have a great bar. Service is very good and fast. They are open late too which is nice for a bite  to eat or for a drink. Very comfortable place. Ample parking.

The Brass Rail makes excellent Lehigh Valley-style cheesesteaks.  It’s an old-school type of restaurant.

Service is efficient and friendly.  

It’s casual and family-run. 

Highly recommended!
Love this place! Food is good, service is great and the prices are reasonable! What more could you ask for?

I have loved brass rail for many years. I am glad to see they have not really changed too much. I was disappointed though in their prices. I have always love their cheesesteak omelette. But the prices have steadily increased to the point i skip going there for breakfast. Its a shame because that was always a family tradition on sunday mornings but not anymore.
